        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 6:11PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 610 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 16 miles southwest of Forder to 13 miles
southwest of Fowler. Movement was northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fowler, Ordway, Manzanola, Olney Springs, and Crowley.

Locally heavy rain will cause ponding of water on roadways and
county roads.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
